flowchart LR
    Sender[Sender<br/>Customer of<br/>Respondent Bank]

    subgraph Respondent [Respondent Bank<br/>Small bank in developing country]
        RespKYC[KYC on Sender<br/>Quality varies]
        RespAML[AML Monitoring<br/>Capacity varies]
    end

    subgraph Correspondent [Correspondent Bank<br/>Large global bank with USD access]
        CorrDD[Due Diligence on<br/>Respondent Bank<br/>Section 312 PATRIOT Act]
        CorrScreen[Transaction Screening<br/>OFAC, sanctions]
        CorrTMS[Transaction Monitoring<br/>Nested accounts,<br/>pass-through activity]
        CorrRisk[Respondent Risk Rating<br/>Jurisdiction, controls,<br/>regulatory environment]
    end

    subgraph Payment [Payment System]
        SWIFT[SWIFT Network]
        Fedwire[Fedwire / CHIPS<br/>USD settlement]
    end

    Beneficiary[Beneficiary<br/>Customer of<br/>receiving bank]

    Sender -->|Wire instruction| Respondent
    Respondent -->|SWIFT MT103<br/>via correspondent| Correspondent
    Correspondent -->|USD clearing| Payment
    Payment -->|Credit| Beneficiary

    CorrDD -.Assesses.-> RespKYC
    CorrDD -.Assesses.-> RespAML

    subgraph Risks [AML Risks in Correspondent Banking]
        Nested[Nested / Payable-Through<br/>Respondent's customers<br/>directly access correspondent]
        Opacity[Opacity<br/>Correspondent cannot see<br/>respondent's end customers]
        DeRisk[De-risking<br/>Correspondent exits relationship<br/>if AML risk too high]
    end

    Correspondent -.Exposed to.-> Risks

    style Correspondent fill:#e3f2fd,stroke:#0d47a1,stroke-width:2px
    style Respondent fill:#fff3e0,stroke:#e65100,stroke-width:2px
    style Risks fill:#ffcdd2,stroke:#b71c1c,stroke-width:2px
